commit.message:
Always show connection ID on pageAction click

Earlier, the connection ID was shown only the first time the page action
was clicked.

Add init.js; move call to start websocket conn there

This moves the little bit of the business logic out of websocket.js so it
doesn't concern itself with when the connection to the server is established.

websocket.js: Make connection inside a function

This will allow calling the function in case the connection was interrupted.
Show dialog box when connected to Alexa

Show the connection ID in words

This will make it obvious that users can say 'one two three four' instead of
'one thousand two hundred and thirty four' for the connection ID 1234.

Move pageAction.onClicked listener to top level

There were cases where the page action click event was not being generated.
This may fix that.
Add debug message for injection status
Dismiss the dialog when Alexa connection is established
addcss.js: Add CSS for jquery ui
Add ui.js with modals that we want to show

Simplify loading of JS files in background.js

Also load jquery-ui
